Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no
need to peel). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{},
then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast
on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway
through cooking.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1} into 6 wedges. Trim the @carrot{2}(trimmed) (no need to peel), quarter
lengthways and then chop into roughly 5cm long batons. Halve the @bell pepper{1}, remove the core and slice into 1cm wide strips. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(chopped) (stalks and all).

Put the @British chicken breasts{2} into a #bowl{} with a glug of @oil{} and half
the @dried thyme{1/2%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Massage the seasoning into your chicken.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat and its packaging.

Pop the red onion, carrot and pepper on a baking tray. Sprinkle on the
remaining @dried thyme{1/2%tsp}, add a glug of @oil{} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Toss to coat the veggies then roast in your oven until soft and
golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). Lay in the chicken breasts and cook
until browned on both sides, ~{2-3%minutes} each side. Once browned, transfer to
your baking tray on top of the veggies and cook for the remaining
~{15-20%minutes}. Don't wash your pan - you need it again in a minute. When the
chicken has 10 minutes left to cook, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}
to the baking tray.

> IMPORTANT: Cook lardons thoroughly. Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

== Sweet Chilli Sauce ==

Whilst the chicken is roasting, add the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{100%ml} to the #chicken frying pan{}, bring to a boil then reduce the heat to a simmer.

Add the @fresh chilli jam{25%g} and stir well to dissolve it (use a #whisk{} if
necessary). Bubble the mixture until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Once cooked, remove the chicken, veg and wedges from your oven.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Cut each chicken breast into five slices. Combine the wedges, vegetables,
bacon lardons and chopped parsley together on one of the baking trays, then
spoon onto plates. Arrange the chicken on top and reheat the sweet chilli
glaze if needed. Spoon the sweet chilli glaze over the chicken and enjoy.

> Mod Step 4: If you've decided to add bacon lardons to your meal, add the
> lardons to the tray with the chicken and veggies when they have 10 mins left
> to cook. IMPORTANT: Cook lardons thoroughly. Wash your hands after handling
> raw meat.

> Mod Step 6: If you've added bacon lardons to your meal, combine the wedges,
> vegetables, bacon lardons and chopped parsley together and continue with the
> rest of the step.